Sentencas: The performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CFC-CGO) composite cathode has been investigated for potential application in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The composite cathodes are prepared and characterized by XRD and SEM, respectively.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of the composite cathodes are investigated using AC impedance and DC polarization methods from 500 to 700 A degrees C under different oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (R (p)) decreases with the increase of CGO content in the composite electrode.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of 40 wt.% CGO in CFC results in the lowest R (p) of 0.48 Omega cm(2) at 700 A degrees C in air.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxygen partial pressure dependence study indicates that the charge-transfer process is the rate limiting step for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: CFC-40CGO composite cathode exhibits the lowest overpotential of about 67 mV at a current density of 85 mA cm(-2) at 700 A degrees C in air.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical performance of Ca2Fe1.4Co0.6O5-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
